WEBVTT

00:00.066 --> 00:05.993
message of the day by Mr. Sean Witt entitled seven powerful prayers in the Bible.

00:06.674 --> 00:07.195
Mr. Witt.

00:14.684 --> 00:15.404
Thank you Curtis.

00:16.145 --> 00:17.207
Good afternoon everyone.

00:17.247 --> 00:23.474
So I think it's interesting Ken's message about praying.

00:24.578 --> 00:27.601
More than interesting, I think it's awesome how God orchestrates these things.

00:28.222 --> 00:30.384
You know, a few weeks ago, I did a message on praying.

00:30.404 --> 00:33.327
I was entitled, The Importance of Prayer.

00:33.808 --> 00:46.121
Well, today, I felt led that I wanted to go ahead and talk about the seven powerful prayers from the Bible that can encourage someone to talk a little bit more about praying.

00:47.523 --> 00:50.826
And I like to give credit where credit is due.

00:52.028 --> 00:54.130
When I was researching for this message,

00:54.370 --> 01:03.562
upon a website called biblepraypoints.com, which kind of gave me a little bit of the outline for this message.

01:05.864 --> 01:06.285
Pardon me.

01:07.526 --> 01:19.922
Okay, so for the first example I'd like to give, let's go to the first prayer, which is Matthew chapter six, verses seven through 13.

01:20.226 --> 01:24.990
And this is one of the prayers that I had in my message a few weeks back as well.

01:27.793 --> 01:35.580
And when you pray, do not use vain repetitions as the heathens do, for they think that they will be heard for their many words.

01:35.981 --> 01:43.488
Therefore, do not be like them, for the Father knows the things you have need of before you ask Him.

01:44.068 --> 01:45.530
In this manner, therefore pray.

01:45.590 --> 01:50.034
Our Father in heaven, hallowed be your name,

01:50.370 --> 01:53.715
Your kingdom come, your will be done on earth as it is in heaven.

01:54.897 --> 01:59.323
Give us our daily, give us this day our daily bread and forgive us of our debts.

02:00.465 --> 02:08.196
And do not lead us into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one for yours is a kingdom and the power and the glory forever.

02:08.316 --> 02:08.657
Amen.

02:10.119 --> 02:12.823
This prayer was taught to us by Jesus himself.

02:14.125 --> 02:15.727
It is a model for all prayers.

02:16.188 --> 02:17.490
It emphasizes

02:18.274 --> 02:28.044
worshiping and having full submission to God's will, having independence and provision for forgiveness and spiritual protection.

02:29.786 --> 02:36.453
So it reminds us to prioritize being in God's kingdom and trusting in Him.

02:36.473 --> 02:38.155
So that's the model prayer.

02:39.036 --> 02:40.878
So now I'd like to go to the second prayer.

02:42.460 --> 02:44.562
And this one is about Hannah.

02:47.682 --> 02:52.369
Hannah's story in the Bible is a testament to her faith and devotion.

02:52.489 --> 02:58.158
She was a wife of Elkinah who had two wives, but Hannah was his favorite.

02:59.379 --> 03:09.615
Despite the taunts and insults from Penonah who had children, Hannah prayed fervently to God seeking a son.

03:09.635 --> 03:17.266
Her prayer was so intense that it caught the attention of the priest Eli who initially

03:17.730 --> 03:19.512
mistook her for being drunk.

03:23.255 --> 03:24.817
Hannah's prayer was answered by God.

03:26.098 --> 03:30.142
She bore a son named Samuel who was dedicated to God as a Nazarite.

03:31.623 --> 03:39.651
Hannah's story is a powerful example of perseverance and prayer and the importance of keeping promises to God.

03:40.952 --> 03:46.738
So let's now go to 1 Samuel 1 verses 8 through 11.

03:50.594 --> 03:54.921
Then Elkanah, her husband, said to her, Hannah, why do you weep?

03:55.321 --> 03:56.242
Why do you not eat?

03:56.583 --> 03:57.945
And why is your heart grieved?

03:59.147 --> 04:01.871
Am I not better to you than 10 sons?

04:02.712 --> 04:06.658
So Hannah rose after they had finished eating and drinking in Shiloh.

04:07.059 --> 04:12.567
And Eli, the priest, was sitting on the seat by the doorpost of the tabernacle of the Lord.

04:13.068 --> 04:18.296
And she was in bitterness of soul and prayed to the Lord and wept in anguish.

04:18.756 --> 04:19.858
Then she made a vow.

04:20.546 --> 04:37.134
She said, O Lord of hosts, if you will indeed look at my affliction of your maidservant and remember me and not forget your maidservant, but will give your maidservant a male child, then I will give him to the Lord all the days of his life and no razor shall come upon his head.

04:38.536 --> 04:47.090
Hannah's prayer is a great example of pouring out her heart to God when we are in desperation and needing to trust him.

04:48.130 --> 04:56.241
Her willingness to surrender, her deepest desire to God's will demonstrates profound faith and devotion.

04:57.062 --> 05:01.488
This is the type of faith and devotion we need to be seeking as well like Hannah did.

05:02.770 --> 05:07.817
So now we're going to go to our third example of prayer.

05:10.401 --> 05:12.163
So this is one's about King David.

05:14.486 --> 05:17.330
And we know that David was a man after God's own heart.

05:18.530 --> 05:20.293
He had his flaws just like we do.

05:22.357 --> 05:30.470
And when his sinful nature was revealed by Nathan, he prayed and he asked for God's forgiveness.

05:30.671 --> 05:32.874
He recognized what he was doing was wrong.

05:33.816 --> 05:39.666
So we're going to go to Psalm 51, and we're going to go ahead and read the chapter of Psalm 51.

05:40.962 --> 05:48.569
Have mercy upon me, O God, according to your loving kindness, according to the multitude of your tender mercies, blot out my transgressions.

05:49.310 --> 06:06.426
Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity and cleanse me from my sin, for I acknowledge my transgressions, and my sin is always before me, and against you, you have only have I sinned and done this evil in your sight, that you may be found just when you speak and blameless when you judge.

06:06.986 --> 06:10.930
Behold, I was brought before in iniquity and in sin,

06:11.170 --> 06:18.603
My mother conceived me, behold, you desire truth in the inward parts, and in the hidden part, you will make me to know wisdom.

06:19.003 --> 06:21.568
Purge me with hissip, and I shall be clean.

06:22.008 --> 06:24.372
Wash me, and I shall be wider than snow.

06:24.973 --> 06:29.481
Make me hear joy and gladness that the bones you have broken may rejoice.

06:30.483 --> 06:37.074
Hide your face for my sins and blot out my iniquities, creating me a clean heart, O Lord, and renew

06:37.634 --> 06:39.256
a steadfast spirit within me.

06:39.276 --> 06:43.563
Do not cast me away from your presence and do not take your Holy Spirit from me."

06:45.185 --> 06:46.667
He's grieving through all this.

06:47.809 --> 06:51.995
Restore me to the joy of your salvation and uphold me in your generous spirit.

06:52.556 --> 07:07.538
Then I will teach transgressors your way and sinners will be converted to you, delivered me from the guilt of bloodshed, O God, to the God of my salvation and my tongue shall sing aloud of your righteousness, O Lord, open my lips.

07:07.650 --> 07:14.239
and my mouth shall show forth your praise, for you do not desire sacrifice, or else I would give it.

07:14.860 --> 07:16.842
You do not delight in burnt offering.

07:16.983 --> 07:21.609
The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit, a broken and contrite heart.

07:22.109 --> 07:24.192
These, O God, you will not despise.

07:24.993 --> 07:32.283
Do good in your pleasure, O Zion, build the walls of Jerusalem, then you shall be pleased with the sacrifices of righteousness and burnt offering.

07:33.044 --> 07:37.490
And burnt offering, then they shall offer bulls on your altar.

07:38.306 --> 07:40.008
this chapter is very powerful.

07:41.890 --> 07:50.238
It was written after David sinned with Bathsheba, which we know resulted in Uriah's death and his son.

07:50.298 --> 08:03.611
David's son dying was the part of the situation, but this prayer is a heartfelt plea for forgiveness and being restored.

08:04.852 --> 08:06.514
It highlights God's mercy,

08:07.394 --> 08:12.800
and the need to have a clean heart, the desire to be renewed in his spirit.

08:13.961 --> 08:27.336
Is a reminder that God is with us even in the midst of sinful acts where there may be consequence for sin, but God will turn his, he won't turn his back on us.

08:27.937 --> 08:36.146
He's waiting for us to acknowledge him and he'll forgive us and help us, but he was wanting us to be seeking him for his help.

08:36.962 --> 08:41.067
So now we're going to go to the fourth prayer, and this involves King Solomon.

08:41.507 --> 08:51.438
You know, in the beginning, King Solomon, at his beginning of his rule, when he was young, he had a great zeal for God, and he was faithful to him.

08:53.220 --> 08:58.366
So now we're going to go to 1 Kings 3, verses 7 through 14.

08:58.406 --> 09:05.234
Now, O Lord, my God, you have a major servant king instead of my father, David.

09:05.378 --> 09:08.703
But I'm a little child, I do not know how to go out and to come in.

09:08.763 --> 09:15.933
And your servant is in the midst of your people whom you have chosen, a great people, too numerous to be numbered or counted.

09:16.434 --> 09:23.424
Therefore, give to your servant an understanding heart to judge your people that I made discern between good and evil.

09:24.245 --> 09:27.570
For who is able to judge this great people of yours?

09:28.431 --> 09:32.978
The speech pleased the Lord that Solomon had asked this thing.

09:33.282 --> 09:47.683
Then God said to him, because you have asked this thing, I have not asked, you have not asked for long life yourself, nor have asked for riches for yourself, nor have asked the life for your enemies, but have asked for yourself understanding to discern justice.

09:48.183 --> 10:01.362
Behold, I have done according to your words, see I have given you a wise and understanding heart so that there has not been anyone like you before, nor shall there be like a rise after you.

10:01.954 --> 10:12.067
And I have also given you what you have not asked, both riches and honor, so that there shall be not anyone like you among the kings all your days.

10:12.447 --> 10:19.276
So if you walk in my ways to keep my statutes and my commandments as your father David walked, then I will lengthen your days.

10:19.576 --> 10:20.597
So as a promise from God.

10:22.179 --> 10:30.610
So when God offered Solomon anything he desired, Solomon asked for wisdom for God's people.

10:31.298 --> 10:40.467
His prayer showed humility, selflessness, and a desire to fulfill God's will rather than seeking personal gain.

10:41.448 --> 10:46.333
Solomon's life example is also a reminder that faithfulness to God must remain.

10:46.373 --> 10:58.706
And as he grew older, he departed from God's commands, which led him astray, as we know, as he started marrying many wives and started doing all of the different

11:01.346 --> 11:07.073
strange things of the idols and gods that weren't our actual God.

11:08.315 --> 11:12.400
So now, let's go on to prayer number five.

11:14.102 --> 11:15.965
This one is regarding Jesus.

11:18.448 --> 11:24.356
So Jesus showed us how to follow God's will when he walked on this earth through his examples.

11:25.537 --> 11:26.258
He did not

11:28.290 --> 11:30.833
He did the complete, excuse me, I have my notes here.

11:30.873 --> 11:31.493
He did not.

11:32.935 --> 11:35.878
He did the complete will, I apologize for that.

11:35.898 --> 11:38.060
He did the complete will of the Father always.

11:38.141 --> 11:39.362
He always said the Father's will.

11:41.244 --> 11:44.247
He followed through with the plan and he saved all mankind.

11:46.670 --> 11:53.757
So now in Matthew 26 verses 36 and 39, we're gonna read the prayer in the Garden of Gethsemane.

11:54.879 --> 11:58.162
Then Jesus came with them to the place called Gethsemane

11:58.562 --> 12:03.208
and said to the disciples, sit here a while, I go and pray over there.

12:03.929 --> 12:09.357
And he took with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, and he began to be sorrowful and deeply distressed.

12:09.777 --> 12:14.043
Then he said to them, my soul is exceedingly sorrowful, even to death.

12:14.524 --> 12:15.826
Stay here and watch for me.

12:15.846 --> 12:25.099
He went a little farther, fell on his face and prayed, saying, oh, my father, if this be possible, let this cup pass for me.

12:25.639 --> 12:27.602
Nevertheless,

12:27.970 --> 12:29.853
Not as I will, but your will.

12:31.516 --> 12:41.711
So even in Christ's darkest hour, Jesus prayed with raw honesty and complete surrender to His Father's will.

12:43.134 --> 12:51.026
This prayer teaches us to teach, to trust God's plan even when it involves suffering or great heartache.

12:56.322 --> 12:58.164
and sacrificing our own will.

12:59.526 --> 13:01.469
You know, this life's not meant to be easy.

13:02.069 --> 13:10.460
There'll be times of heartache, like I mentioned in agony, but we must follow Jesus' example of following God's will, always.

13:11.882 --> 13:13.384
So now on to prayer number six.

13:13.965 --> 13:15.527
This involves the Apostle Paul.

13:16.748 --> 13:24.498
Paul wrote the book of Ephesians to help affirm the Ephesian believers to be faithful, the main focus

13:24.930 --> 13:29.255
is being in Christ, and he wrote this while he was under house arrest.

13:30.156 --> 13:33.940
So now we're going to go to Ephesians chapter 3, verses 13 through 19.

13:36.863 --> 13:44.452
Therefore I ask that you do not lose heart at my tribulations for you, which is your glory.

13:45.373 --> 13:54.002
For this reason I bow my needs to the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, from whom the whole family in heaven and earth is named.

13:54.242 --> 14:21.970
that he would grant you according to the riches of his glory to be strengthened with might through his spirit in the inner man, that Christ may dwell in your hearts through faith, that you being rooted and grounded in love may be able to comprehend with all the saints what is the width and length and depth and height to know the love of Jesus Christ, which passes knowledge that you may be filled with all the fullness of God.

14:23.234 --> 14:32.308
Paul's prayer for the Ephesians is a powerful intercession for spiritual growth, rooted in God's love and power.

14:33.951 --> 14:41.663
It reminds us to be using God's gift to the Holy Spirit and seeking deeper intimacy with Christ and God the Father daily.

14:43.306 --> 14:45.610
So now we come to our last one, the seventh prayer.

14:45.630 --> 14:50.898
And this one is the prayer of J. Bez.

14:53.314 --> 14:57.280
And I got this brief description of J. Bess from Crosswalk.com.

14:58.662 --> 15:08.236
The prayer of J. Bess is a brief but profound petition found in the Old Testament of the Bible, specifically in 1 Chronicles 4, verse 10.

15:08.917 --> 15:13.705
It is named after J. Bess who was mentioned in a genealogical record in Chronicles.

15:14.266 --> 15:22.578
Despite the brief mention of his life, J. Bess's prayer stands out for his heartfelt plea to God for blessing and guidance.

15:23.874 --> 15:27.618
So now we're going to read 1 Chronicles 4 verses 9 through 10.

15:29.439 --> 15:38.708
Now, J. Bez was more honorable than his brothers and his mother called his name, J. Bez, saying, because I bore him in pain.

15:38.768 --> 15:52.882
And J. Bez called on the God of Israel, saying, oh, that you would bless me indeed and enlarge my territory, that your hand would be on me and that you would keep me from evil, that I may not cause pain.

15:53.218 --> 15:55.340
So God granted him what he requested.

15:56.682 --> 16:01.948
J. Bez simple yet bold prayer demonstrates faith in God.

16:02.008 --> 16:06.153
It's ability to bless, protect, and guide us.

16:07.314 --> 16:12.000
It encourages us to ask God for his favor and provision in our lives.

16:12.440 --> 16:14.442
God wants us to ask for his blessing.

16:14.883 --> 16:16.585
He wants to give the very best to us.

16:17.986 --> 16:21.170
So why are these prayers truly powerful?

16:23.362 --> 16:30.068
These prayers are powerful because they reflect the aspects of a thriving relationship with God, our Father.

16:32.951 --> 16:35.534
We have surrender and worship.

16:35.554 --> 16:37.756
That's the Lord's prayer that I read.

16:38.877 --> 16:42.621
Repentance and honesty from David's prayer.

16:44.162 --> 16:47.165
Trust and faith from Hannah and J. Bez's prayer.

16:49.027 --> 16:52.370
Wisdom and selflessness from Solomon's prayer.

16:53.762 --> 16:57.426
and then love and spiritual growth from Paul's prayer.

16:58.767 --> 17:13.643
So in conclusion, these prayers teach us how to approach God with faith, humility, and a heart to align with the will of what he is doing.

17:14.904 --> 17:20.850
They remind us that praying to God isn't just about asking, but about connecting with God's heart.

